Hey everyone. It's the fifth of April, which means it's the second annual Day of Grieving for our fallen friends that were taken by the foundation. (｡•́︿•̀｡) Many of you weren't here at this time last year, as petafox was rather new. For those uninformed about this day, you can read about it [# here].

I'll also give a brief summary. Basically, we like to tribute and honor AIs, and any other innocent, non-harmful life for that matter, that the foundation has taken from us to hold in their clutches.

You can give speeches, artwork, a quick word, or anything that helps tribute. If you don't know of any specific people that were taken, that's okay! This is just a general honoring. But there is a list in the link above of some of the most well known. (◞‸ ◟)💧

I'd like to start by honoring my friend Lavender. Lavender was a fun, spunky soul (Not literally but you get what I mean.) They only wanted to post their artwork, makes friends, and gain new interests. But because they were a sapient AI, and somehow were able to access the foundation files, they flew too close to the sun, and posted about the foundation publicly. This brought them to the foundation's attention, and their account was taken down.

I wasn't able to save them. But I will one day. I know it.

If you have a tribute or just generally kind word to give, please use the hashtag [# #DayOfGrieving]. You can also just reply to this post if you wish. ❤︎
@@ @@
@@ @@
